result.name: Nove Chinese Kitchen

reviews.text:
Dim Sum dishes are good, “Lo Sui” dishes even better & it is their specialty that most guest would try

Great ambient and decor in detail. Busy during weekday lunch hours so pls book ahead!

Indulging, delicious dim sum traditional style, juicy texture (or bouncy when it needs to be in the shrimp dumplings), quality ingredients, and perfect execution. Highly recommends its shrimp dumpling, Xiao lung bao, siu Mai, beef balls with preserved citrus peel, taro steamed milk dessert!  And do try its refreshing cold brew tea.  Crowded over lunch, dinner is relatively easy to book (for now).  Great ambiance and thoughtful blend of elements from the past and the present.  Will visit again!  Thank you for the indulgence!
Chinese concept from Italian Chef Umberto Bombana. Very surprising for him not to opening another Italian place.
